  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Mignon's on a hillside in the pedestrianised centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/4c9fc09241f14e3c80acb89b5c9226dd" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4c9fc09241f14e3c80acb89b5c9226dd}" title="Selva">Selva</a>. The hotel's ideal location means exploring the town or venturing off into the mountains couldn't be easier. Selva has lots to offer and being a World Heritage Site, the views come as standard. Head into the mountains where there are walking routes for everyone to enjoy.</p>
<h2>Family run with local food &amp; drink</h2>
<p>Owners Giorgio and Enrica have paid great attention to detail to create a comfortable and stylish atmosphere at this hotel. The cosy dining room serves up traditional cuisine that uses locally sourced produce and the bar is the perfect place to relax while trying some of the fantastic wine labels from hotel's cellar. Each room has a balcony which means you can enjoy views of the town, valley or mountains from the comfort of your own room.</p>
<h2>Relax &amp; unwind in the mountains</h2>
<p>If relaxation is more on your mind, make sure you take advantage of the state-of-the-art spa where you’ll find a heated indoor pool and saunas. The hotel interiors are sophisticated and there are plenty of spots to unwind after a busy day exploring, including the garden where you can sit back and relax with a drink.</p>]]></description>
