  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Standard Rooms </strong>are about 25<span>m² and sleep two people. They are decorated in either a contemporary style with hardwood floors, solid oak furniture and minimalist design, or in a traditional style with wooden beams, carpets and warm colours.</span></p>
<p><strong>Comfort Rooms</strong> are about 27m² and can sleep up to two people. </p>
<p><strong>Premium Rooms</strong> are about 35m² and sleep up to three people (extra bed is a single sofa bed). These rooms have high quality furnishings and views over the village.</p>
<p><strong>Superior Rooms</strong> are about 40m² and can sleep up to four people (extra bed is a double sofa bed). Each room is individually decorated with special touches such as traditional wood stoves and stylish wooden walls. </p>
<p><strong>Single Rooms</strong> are 20m² and are a great choice for solo travellers.</p>
<p><span><strong>Standard Rooms for Sole Use</strong> are available on request, please call to book. </span></p>
<p>Most rooms have twin beds, please pre-advise if you would prefer a double. </p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Balcony</li>
<li>Shower</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Bathrobes &amp; slippers</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Safe</li>
</ul>
<p>Cots are available on request for approx. €45 per day, payable locally. </p>
<p><strong>Local fees &amp; taxes</strong></p>
<p>A resort tax of approx. €3.40 per person per day is payable locally.</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>]]></roomsDescription>
